caption.p: Overlapped chromatograms of the representative samples of the root barks ( A), the twigs ( B), the fruits ( C), and the leaves ( D) of the Morus samples at the detection wavelength of 265 nm; 1, skimmin; 2, mulberroside A; 3, chlorogenic acid; 4, 4-hydroxycinnamic acid; 5, rutin; 6, taxifolin; 7, isoquercitrin; 8, oxyresveratrol; 9, astragalin; 10, quercitrin; 11, kuwanon G; 12, morusin.
